{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"26d0029d-f9ef-4851-a324-68d0eae4d5c6","content":"Good news — on .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01AdwQ2WFb3SXGcEX91tE4Zr","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_014KcUQ6fDXjNZWqKxfgfqgN","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7a33e2d1a0194aa5beaad3ef07a78930/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7a33e2d1a0194aa5beaad3ef07a78930/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a7e62f69-9d43-484a-a663-154b9c699945","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to opt into MTP support with `dotnet test`. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior, so the property is no longer needed.\n\n\nI'll walk them through the necessary changes to their project file to clean this up.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"3401:2F6FBA:757A237:81CA8B2:69F3FB80"},"id":"87a9ca06-b6a6-4c5a-a6a9-ade199f016bd","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:01:59.238Z","parentId":"7baf791f-173b-42e3-8925-555c70759f75"}
